07/11/2003
ATHENS, Greece -- FBI Director Robert Mueller arrived in Athens on Thursday (6 November) to inspect security arrangements for the 2004 Summer Olympics. A police spokesman said he would be meeting senior law enforcement officials and would tour the Olympic sites. The United States and six other nations are advising Greek organisers on security issues. Just hours before Mueller's arrival, a series of firebombs damaged three banks in central Athens.
In other news Thursday, parliament ratified the accession protocol of seven new NATO countries -- Bulgaria, Estonia, Latvia, Lithuania, Romania, Slovakia and Slovenia. Greece is the 13th Alliance member to do so. (AP, Reuters, ANA, MPA, bTV - 06/11/03)
